sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>Ports: 6379, 8265, 8000, 10001
    participant WorkerPods as Ray Worker Pods
    participant Redis as Redis (optional)<br/>6379/TCP

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 1: RayCluster Provisioning

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (RayCluster)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create head-svc (Headless/ClusterIP)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route/Ingress (dashboard)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    WorkerPods->>HeadPod: GCS connection<br/>TCP 6379 (plaintext)
    Note right of HeadPod: Cluster is ready

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 2: RayJob Submission (K8sJobMode)

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (RayJob)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster (if needed)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create K8s submitter Job<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Note right of K8sAPI: Submitter Job Pod starts
    K8sAPI->>HeadPod: ray job submit<br/>HTTP 8265/TCP (plaintext)
    loop Every 3 seconds
        Operator->>HeadPod: Poll job status<br/>HTTP GET 8265/TCP (plaintext)
        HeadPod-->>Operator: Job status response
    end
    Note right of Operator: Job completes → update CR status

    Note over User,Redis: Flow 3: RayService Zero-Downtime Upgrade

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply RayService (updated)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (RayService)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create pending RayCluster<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Note right of K8sAPI: Pending cluster provisions
    Operator->>HeadPod: Deploy serve app config<br/>HTTP PUT 8265/TCP (plaintext)
    loop Every 2 seconds
        Operator->>HeadPod: Health check serve proxy<br/>HTTP GET 8000/TCP -/healthz
        HeadPod-->>Operator: Health status
    end
    Note right of Operator: Pending cluster healthy
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update Service selector → pending cluster<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Delete old RayCluster<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Note right of Operator: Zero-downtime upgrade complete

    Note over User,Redis: Optional: GCS Fault Tolerance

    HeadPod->>Redis: Persist GCS state<br/>TCP 6379 (password optional)
    Redis-->>HeadPod: ACK
